<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-2405] KafkaHealthCheck kills the JVM in handleSessionEstablishmentError</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2405</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The current code in KafkaHealthCheck in trunk does this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;override def handleSessionEstablishmentError(error: Throwable): Unit = {
      fatal(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Could not establish session with zookeeper&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, error)
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;System&lt;/span&gt;.exit(-1)
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thus terminating the JVM. A session establishment error shouldn&apos;t cause the JVM to terminate.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
